+# Similarity & Calibration
+
+## Semantic Equivalence
+ECL uses embeddings to classify claim pairs:
+
+- **equivalent**: cosine ≥ 0.95
+- **related**: 0.85–0.95
+- **different**: < 0.85
+
+Backends:
+- `sentence-transformers` (default, `ECL_ST_MODEL`, e.g. `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`)
+- OpenAI embeddings (`ECL_OPENAI_EMBED_MODEL`, e.g. `text-embedding-3-small`)
+
+Set `ECL_EMBED_BACKEND=sentence-transformers|openai`.
+
+## Consensus Score
+Consensus now aggregates pairwise labels:
+`equivalent = 1.0`, `related = 0.5`, `different = 0.0`, normalized to [0,1].
+
+## Calibration
+Two baselines are provided:
+- **Isotonic regression** for non-parametric calibration
+- **Platt scaling** (logistic) for parametric calibration
+
+Use these in the evaluation harness to report before/after ECE and plot reliability curves.
+
